{"assignees":[{"id":"U_kgDOB9cnnw","login":"yersonargotev","name":"Yerson Argote","databaseId":131540895}],"body":"## Parent\n\n#49\n\n## What to build\n\nOpen the controlled Packy cutover window and produce a durable baseline evidence bundle before any identity mutation. Freeze ordinary releases and pack-source synchronization, rule out conflicting external state, bind the exact Matty base and Packy candidate inputs, and prove the historical recovery path remains usable.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Ordinary releases and pack-source synchronization are frozen, with the permitted v0.1.7 path documented.\n- [ ] The Packy repository, tap, Homebrew-core, Pages, and workflow-run state are rechecked immediately before execution; any collision or active conflicting run blocks progress.\n- [ ] The exact pre-rename base SHA and intended candidate inputs are recorded with timestamps, tool versions, commands, exit statuses, and complete outputs or durable log links.\n- [ ] Historical Matty v0.1.6 formula, release assets, checksums, executable, and tag SHA are proven obtainable and mutually consistent.\n- [ ] The issue #52 maintainer recovery material and approved paths are verified without modifying real user configuration.\n- [ ] The evidence states that automation remains frozen until the final audit ticket completes.\n\n## Blocked by\n\nNone — can start immediately.","labels":[{"id":"LA_kwDOTOgLZM8AAAACqy8g-w","name":"status:approved","description":"Issue is approved for implementation","color":"0E8A16"}],"number":56,"state":"OPEN","title":"Freeze and bind the Packy cutover window","url":"https://github.com/yersonargotev/matty/issues/56"}
